01:01:29.830 --> 01:01:32.800
So if I take my
Wannier function,

01:01:32.800 --> 01:01:35.770
which is built out of
eigenvalues for that equation,

01:01:35.770 --> 01:01:38.245
[INAUDIBLE] bunch
of energy terms.

01:01:38.245 --> 01:01:40.720
On every site [INAUDIBLE]
they're the same.

01:01:40.720 --> 01:01:43.690
Because you have a common
[INAUDIBLE] energy that you can

01:01:43.690 --> 01:01:44.720
[INAUDIBLE].

01:01:44.720 --> 01:01:46.886
AUDIENCE: Well then just
multiple it by [INAUDIBLE].

01:01:51.120 --> 01:01:53.340
PROFESSOR: My gut
feeling is-- and this

01:01:53.340 --> 01:01:55.580
is why nobody considers
it-- it's just

01:01:55.580 --> 01:01:59.660
a constant energy, which is
probably something like the 0

01:01:59.660 --> 01:02:02.150
point energy times the number
of particles, which is not

01:02:02.150 --> 01:02:03.600
affecting any dynamics.

01:02:03.600 --> 01:02:06.510
It's pretty much a constant
which can be simply dropped.

01:02:11.814 --> 01:02:13.230
Let me just go
